This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the segmentation of neuroanatomy in T1-weighted magnetic resonance images using a deep convolutional neural network. The paper also involves end-to-end learning-based approaches, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the use of stochastic gradient descent for learning the parameters of the network suggests a connection to neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves the use of 3D imaging techniques, which may be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM).
